    "# L3 M4.3: Change Management & Compliance\n",
    "\n",
    "## Learning Arc\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:** Build a GCC-grade change management system that transforms RAG deployments from 'cowboy coding' to 'audit-ready governance' - preventing compliance disasters like the 3 AM scenario where an unapproved embedding model change resulted in ₹2.5 crore SOX 404 fines and executive terminations.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Concepts Covered:**\n",
    "- **Change Types:** Standard (pre-approved), Normal (requires approval), Emergency (critical)\n",
    "- **6-Phase Workflow:** Request → Impact Assessment → Approval → Implementation → Verification → Review\n",
    "- **Compliance-Aware Rollback:** 5 automated triggers (compliance failure, metrics degraded, security compromised, user complaints, audit gaps)\n",
    "- **Change Advisory Board (CAB):** Multi-stakeholder approval process with 7 member roles\n",
    "- **Immutable Audit Trail:** 7-10 year retention for regulatory compliance (SOX, GDPR, DPDPA)\n",
    "\n",
    "**After Completing This Notebook:**\n",
    "- You will understand the 3 change types and when each applies\n",
    "- You can implement the 6-phase change management workflow\n",
    "- You will build approval routing logic for Standard/Normal/Emergency changes\n",
    "- You can create rollback criteria detection with 5 automated triggers\n",
    "- You will generate compliance-ready audit trails with immutable logging\n",
    "- You can execute end-to-end changes from request to closure\n",
    "\n",
    "**Context in Track L3.M4:**\n",
    "This module builds on AI Governance & Risk Management (M4.1) and Vendor Risk Assessment (M4.2), completing the Enterprise Integration track with operational change control processes."
   ]
