    "## Section 4: Concept 3 - Compliance-Aware Rollback (5 Automated Triggers)\n",
    "\n",
    "Rollback in a GCC must preserve compliance, not just revert code.\n",
    "\n",
    "**5 Rollback Triggers:**\n",
    "1. **Compliance Test Failure** - PII detection accuracy <98%, encryption validation failed\n",
    "2. **Metrics Degraded >20%** - Latency or error rate increased >20%\n",
    "3. **Security Controls Compromised** - Audit logs stopped, access controls bypassed\n",
    "4. **User Complaints >10/hour** - Support tickets indicating incorrect results\n",
    "5. **Audit Log Gaps** - Missing logs during deployment window\n",
    "\n",
    "When triggered, automatic rollback executes in <15 minutes and verifies compliance after rollback."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Scenario 1: Compliance test failure\n",
    "print(\"Scenario 1: PII detection accuracy dropped below threshold\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics = {\n",
    "    \"compliance_tests_passed\": False,  # PII detection failed\n",
    "    \"pii_detection_accuracy\": 87.3,    # Below 98% threshold\n",
    "}\n",
    "baseline_metrics = {\n",
    "    \"compliance_tests_passed\": True,\n",
    "    \"pii_detection_accuracy\": 98.5,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "trigger = RollbackDetector.check_rollback_triggers(metrics, baseline_metrics)\n",
    "print(f\"Rollback Trigger: {trigger.value if trigger else 'None'}\")\n",
    "# Expected: compliance_test_failure\n",
    "\n",
    "if trigger:\n",
    "    rollback_result = RollbackDetector.execute_rollback(\n",
    "        change_id=\"CHG-DEMO-001\",\n",
    "        trigger=trigger,\n",
    "        offline=True  # Simulate rollback\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nRollback Executed: {rollback_result['rollback_executed']}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Compliance Verified After Rollback: {rollback_result['compliance_verified']}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50 + \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scenario 2: Latency degraded >20%\n",
    "print(\"Scenario 2: Latency increased by 81% (3.8s vs 2.1s baseline)\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics = {\n",
    "    \"latency\": 3.8,\n",
    "    \"compliance_tests_passed\": True,\n",
    "}\n",
    "baseline_metrics = {\n",
    "    \"latency\": 2.1,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "trigger = RollbackDetector.check_rollback_triggers(metrics, baseline_metrics)\n",
    "print(f\"Rollback Trigger: {trigger.value if trigger else 'None'}\")\n",
    "# Expected: metrics_degraded\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50 + \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scenario 3: No rollback triggers (healthy deployment)\n",
    "print(\"Scenario 3: Healthy deployment - no rollback needed\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics = {\n",
    "    \"latency\": 2.2,  # Only 4.8% increase\n",
    "    \"error_rate\": 0.8,\n",
    "    \"compliance_tests_passed\": True,\n",
    "    \"audit_logs_recording\": True,\n",
    "    \"support_tickets_per_hour\": 3,\n",
    "}\n",
    "baseline_metrics = {\n",
    "    \"latency\": 2.1,\n",
    "    \"error_rate\": 0.7,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "trigger = RollbackDetector.check_rollback_triggers(metrics, baseline_metrics)\n",
    "print(f\"Rollback Trigger: {trigger.value if trigger else 'None'}\")\n",
    "print(\"âœ" Deployment successful - no rollback needed\")\n",
    "# Expected: None"
   ]
